@Sunshow Thanks for your suggestion , `@Reference` is like `@Autowired` ， `@Autowired` is also not controlled by `@ComponentScan` with base packages，you can refer this method ：
`org.springframework.context.annotation.AnnotationConfigUtils#registerAnnotationConfigProcessors(org.springframework.beans.factory.support.BeanDefinitionRegistry, java.lang.Object)` , `AutowiredAnnotationBeanPostProcessor` was registered by Spring Framework.

Consider this scene, Some components were declared in Spring's XML configuration files , they used `@Reference` to inject Dubbo Services, If the base packages were specified in `@DubboComponentScan` , those components were ignore, it's unreasonable.
